cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.LG

This paper discusses the representation and reasoning of social norms in the context of human-robot interactions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development of intelligent agents such as robots. The paper also involves planning and execution of behavior, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of institutions as a formal framework for defining and encapsulating norms, which could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the use of formal computational frameworks, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
